            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What does it mean for a variable to have a local scope?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">We can't access or update it outside of the function where it was created</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">We can access it from anywhere in the code</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">We can't access or update it outside of the function where it was created.</p></body></html>"
