          {
            "title": "Global scope 1",
            "id": 86994,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Variables created outside of a function block have a <strong>global scope</strong>, like <code>shipping</code> here.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"shipping = \" /><text value=\"10\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"calculate_total\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(cart)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" print(cart + shipping)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"calculate_total(\" /><text value=\"54\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"8\" /><option startIndex=\"9\" endIndex=\"10\" /><option startIndex=\"11\" endIndex=\"13\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"64\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>shipping</code>, followed by <code>=</code>, and finally <code>10</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Global access",
            "id": 86995,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>With a global scope, we can safely <strong>access</strong> the variable anywhere in the code, as we did with <code>shipping</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"shipping = \" /><text value=\"10\" class=\"number\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"def\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"calculate_total\" class=\"title\" /><text value=\"(cart)\" class=\"params\" /><text value=\":\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" print(cart + shipping)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"calculate_total(\" /><text value=\"54\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"56\" endIndex=\"64\" /></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>shipping</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Global scope 2",
            "id": 86996,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>All variables have a global scope, except for those created inside functions, like player_1 here.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"single_player = \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"if\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" single_player:\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" player_1 = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Mario&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"f&quot;Player 1: \" /><text value=\"{player_1}\" class=\"subst\" /><text value=\"&quot;\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"41\" endIndex=\"49\" /><option startIndex=\"50\" endIndex=\"51\" /><option startIndex=\"52\" endIndex=\"59\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Player 1: Mario\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>player_1</code>, followed by <code>=</code>, and finally <code>\"Mario\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Access after creating",
            "id": 86997,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Even with a global scope, it's important that we can only access variables after we create them, like here with <code>character</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"character = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Mario&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(character)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"19\" /><option startIndex=\"20\" endIndex=\"36\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"if\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Mario\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>character = \"Mario\"</code>, followed by <code>print(character)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
